This paper deals with the detection of DDoS attacks on network links, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of machine learning algorithms for attack detection suggests a possible fit with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the analysis of network traffic, which could be relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper presents analytical and emulated results, which could be relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
